Standard and Poor's Corp said itdowngraded to CCC-plus from B-minus Hyponex Corp's 30 mln dlrsof subordinated debt.    It assigned a CCC-plus rating to Hyponex's 150 mln dlrs ofsenior subordinated debentures due 1999 that were pricedWednesday for offering. The implied senior debt rating is B.    S and P cited an increase in debt leverage to 86 pct ofcapitalization from 56 pct. While the company's operatingrecord has been successful, S and P said the action alsoreflected uncertainties and risks associated with management'snew business and investment strategies. Reuter&#3;